      "name": "Literature-based assessment of FEA compression-bending predictive capability",
      "description": "A structured survey of published finite-element studies of spinal implant compression-bending under ASTM F1717 conditions was conducted. Fifteen peer-reviewed publications were identified and reviewed to characterize the typical predictive accuracy of FEA models for construct stiffness and yield force. The review concluded that FEA models of this class routinely achieve agreement within 8–12% of bench-measured values, supporting confidence in the present model's outputs. No direct comparison to the N=11 physical constructs was performed as part of this activity.",
